Veteran Actor Dhamendra Tags Vinesh Phogat As 'Daughter Of The Soil' After Wife Hema Malini Faces Backlash

Veteran actor Dharmendra pens a heartfelt note for Vinesh Phogat after Paris Olympics 2024 disqualification. The veteran actor took to Instagram, shared a picture of Phogat calling her a "Brave, adventurous daughter of the soil". His post came after wife Hema Malini's "100 gms matters a lot" comment. Let us have a look at what were the reactions and how this particular post came across.

Katie Price Detained at Heathrow for Skipping Court; Faces Bankruptcy Fallout

Katie Price, a 46-year-old former model, has been arrested at Heathrow Airport upon her return from Turkey, where she had traveled for a cosmetic procedure. The arrest stems from her failure to appear in court. A warrant for her arrest was issued on July 30 due to her no-show at a court hearing related to her bankruptcies. Reports indicate that the judge issued the warrant after noting that Price had not provided an explanation for her absence. Price had been declared bankrupt previously in November 2019 and again in March 2024. Take a look at the video...

PM Modi’s Resounding Praise for Wrestler Vinesh Phogat Amid Her Disqualification at the Paris Olympics

India's Honourable Prime Minister Narendra Modi showered praise on wrestler Vinesh Phogat, amid her disqualification at the Paris Olympics 2024. Despite the setback, PM Modi highlighted her dedication, resilience and incredible journey in the world of sports. This heartening acknowledgment underscores the importance of perseverance and national pride. Check out PM’s encouraging words.

Abhishek Bachchan's Alleged Divorce Announcement Video Sparks Outrage: AI-Generated Clip Sparks Controversy

A video claiming that Abhishek Bachchan announced his divorce from Aishwarya Rai has gone viral online. The video, which features noticeable lip-syncing issues, spread rapidly and has been widely condemned by netizens who suspect it may be a fake. Abhishek is not alone in facing AI-related manipulation; earlier, celebrities such as Aamir Khan, Ranveer Singh, Rashmika Mandanna, Katrina Kaif, and Kajol also fell victim to deepfake technology. Rumours about Ash and Abhi’s relationship have been trending on social media for some time. Recently, the mother-daughter duo enjoyed a vacation in New York without Abhishek and were notably distant from the Bachchans at the Ambani wedding. Abhishek's recent like on a divorce-related post has further fueled the buzz. On the work front, Abhishek will next be seen in Remo D'Souza's film 'Be Happy.'
